    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3 class="faq-question">How long does it take to get a driver's license?</h3>
        <p class="faq-answer">The time required to obtain a driver's license varies based on individual learning pace, lesson frequency, and the specific requirements of your country or region. On average, most learners need <strong>20 to 40 hours</strong> of professional instruction combined with private practice. Some students opt for <strong>intensive driving courses</strong> to fast-track their learning, while others prefer a gradual approach over several months.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3 class="faq-question">What are the requirements to start driving lessons?</h3>
        <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>To begin your driving lessons, you typically need to meet the following criteria:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Be of the minimum legal driving age in your country (e.g., <strong>17 years</strong> in most European countries).</li>
            <li>Possess a valid provisional or learner’s permit.</li>
            <li>Pass an eyesight test to ensure you meet the required visual standards.</li>
            <li>Provide identification documents such as a passport or national ID card.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
        <h3 class="faq-question">Do I need a provisional license to start learning?</h3>
        <p class="faq-answer">Yes, in most European countries, a <strong>provisional driving license</strong> is required before taking any lessons on public roads. This license allows you to practice driving under supervision and is typically obtained by applying through your local transport authority, such as the <strong>DVLA in the UK</strong>. You will need to provide identity documents and pass a vision test to receive your provisional license.</p>
    </div>
